cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code, the trained model, or build on the methodology or findings, please cite this repository."
title: "Mouse Trajectory Synthesis: an event-stream generative model indistinguishable from human movement at the kinematic level"
authors:
  - family-names: "Lau"
    given-names: "Aaron"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-07
url: "https://github.com/4LAU/mouse-trajectory-synthesis"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - mouse dynamics
  - trajectory synthesis
  - generative models
  - masked transformer
  - human motor control
abstract: >-
  A 6M-parameter masked bidirectional Transformer over polar event streams
  generates point-to-point mouse trajectories that a Random Forest detector
  cannot distinguish from held-out human movement (OOB AUC 0.504 at n=2000,
  confirmed across three seeds) after set-level adversarial reselection over
  cached candidate pools. The repository includes the evaluation framework,
  the full experiment journal, trained weights, and cached pools that
  reproduce the headline number on CPU in minutes.
